4 SYNOPSIS:
5 The Alabama Resilience Council was established
6 by Executive Order No. 736 to provide a forum for
7 coordinating activities of state government and for
8 facilitating interactions between state and local
9 government and the private sector to proactively
10 address harmful impacts on Alabama communities and
11 infrastructure before they occur.
12 This bill would permanently establish the
13 Alabama Resilience Council as an appointed advisory
14 group within the executive branch of state government.
15 This bill would also provide for the rules,
16 duties, and procedures of the council.
17 This bill would also authorize appointment of,
18 and provide for the responsibilities of, a Chief
19 Resilience Officer.
20 This bill would also require a statewide
21 resilience plan that includes a statewide comprehensive
22 risk and vulnerability assessment.
23
24
25 A BILL
26 TO BE ENTITLED
27 AN ACT
