HB179 INTRODUCED
29 To create the Alabama Resilience Council as an
30 appointed advisory group within the executive branch of state
31 government, and to provide for the rules, duties, and
32 procedures of the council; to authorize appointment of, and
33 provide for the responsibilities of, a Chief Resilience
34 Officer; to require a statewide resilience plan that includes
35 a statewide comprehensive risk and vulnerability assessment.
36 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
37 Section 1. The Legislature finds and declares the
38 following:
39 (a) Alabama is susceptible to various natural and
40 manmade disaster events, posing threats to the safety of its
41 citizens, integrity of its infrastructure, prospects for its
42 economic growth, and maintenance and protection of its unique
43 natural resources. These threats also pose significant fiscal
44 and operational risks to functions of the state and local
45 government.
46 (b) For the purposes of this Act, the term “resilience”
47 shall be considered the capacity of individuals, communities,
48 businesses, and systems to anticipate, prepare for, adapt to,
49 and rapidly recover from adverse events. For the purposes of
50 this Act, resilience shall be guided by five principles:
51 individual responsibility; collective continuity and function;
52 factual assessment of risk; integrated resilience efforts; and
53 focused support.
54 (c) The Alabama Resilience Council established by
55 Executive Order No. 736, May 5, 2023, has examined resilience
56 policy needs to address current and future adverse events, and
Page 2

policy needs to address current and future adverse events, and
HB179 INTRODUCED
57 based on its findings, Alabama would benefit from a lasting,
58 comprehensive approach to resilience.
59 (d) Coordinated statewide resilience efforts and
60 development of a statewide resilience plan would be most
61 effective under a single designated Chief Resilience Officer
62 to coordinate activities of the Alabama Resilience Council.
63 Section 2. (a) Commencing upon the Governor’s
64 rescission of Executive Order No. 736, the Alabama Resilience
65 Council shall be created as an appointed advisory group within
66 the executive branch of state government for the purpose of
67 coordinating resilience-related activities of state government
68 and for facilitating interactions between state and local
69 government and the private sector to proactively address
70 harmful impacts on Alabama communities and infrastructure
71 before they occur.
72 (b) The voting members of the council shall consist of
73 the Governor or his or her designee, the Chief Resilience
74 Officer, and the head of the following agencies or their
75 designees:
76 (1) The Alabama Department of Agriculture and
77 Industries.
78 (2) The Alabama Department of Commerce.
79 (3) The Alabama Department of Conservation and Natural
80 Resources.
81 (4) The Alabama Department of Economic and Community
82 Affairs.
83 (5) The Alabama Department of Environmental Management.
84
