253 Fund” to be used to support the activities of the Alabama
254 Resilience Council and the Office of the Chief Resilience
255 Officer. The Chief Resilience Officer and the Council are
256 authorized to receive and to deposit into or disburse from the
257 Fund any federal, state, or private monies, in accordance with
258 applicable law. Receipts deposited into this fund shall be
259 disbursed only by warrants of the state Comptroller drawn upon
260 the State Treasury on itemized vouchers approved by the Chief
261 Resilience Officer. No funds deposited pursuant to Section
262 27-2-39 shall be withdrawn or expended except as budgeted and
263 allotted according to Sections 41-4-80 to 41-4-96, inclusive,
264 and 41-19-1 to 41-19-12, inclusive, and only in amounts as
265 stipulated in the general fund appropriations act or other
266 appropriation acts. At the end of each fiscal year, any
267 unencumbered and unexpended balance shall not revert to the
268 State General Fund under Section 41-4-93, but shall carry over
269 to the next fiscal year.
